text: Vallée-de-Ronsard is a commune in the Loir-et-Cher department of central France. It was established on 1 January 2019 by merger of the former communes of Couture-sur-Loir (the seat) and Tréhet.Arrêté préfectoral 29 November 2018 ==See also== *Communes of the Loir-et-Cher department ==References== *INSEE statistics Category:Communes of Loir-et-Cher
title: Vallée-de-Ronsard
